    <!--75-->Goblin Scimitar x4<br />
    Cave Troll Hammer    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">The fellowship in this deck is really not tricky except for that Nazgul player you tear to pieces.  The 4 Defiances in the deck are deffinately for Arwen the Machine.  Generally you just play what you draw.  I would try to outbid your opponent at the beginning so you pull the Green Dragon Inn (the actual bid is usually 3, but it can vary opponent to opponent).  Also, don&#39;t ever play 6 companions (aka Sam likes Lurtz and on Saturday and Sunday, the Witch King) and attempt not to get 5 burdens for my friend and yours, Enquea (I believe he will be a silver bullet in many decks).  Other than that, the deck plays itself.<br />
On to the fun part, Moria!!!!!!<br />
Obviosly try to get down your helper cards early, but watch for Dreary and Sleep.  Be careful not to lose all of your minions in simple damage dealing before you have a swars or are at site 4.  This is the point some overlook.  This deck only runs 17 minions and only 14 can be stacked on swarms.  Moria Orcs are fairly simple to play once you understand the minion/nonminion ration in the version of swarms you are playing.  And a final note, don&#39;t worry about Greenleaf and Aragorn&#39;s Machine gun if they are at site 4, make them use it and proceed to obliterate tham at the Bridge.  Good Hunting. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
